Step 5: Create the Frontend (index.html)
📋 Instructions
Goal: To create the HTML file that will be your user interface. This file will be served by Flask and will allow you to send requests to your backend.

Make sure you are in your project directory (~/ai_assistant).

Create a new file named index.html using a text editor (e.g., nano index.html).

Copy all the code from the block below and paste it into this new index.html file.

How this file works:

HTML: Creates the basic page structure: a title, two text inputs (for project path and your prompt), a "Generate" button, and a <div> to show the results.

CSS: A small <style> block is included to make it look clean and usable.

JavaScript: A <script> block at the bottom contains all the logic. It waits for you to click the button, then it:

Gets the text from the input boxes.

Uses fetch() to send this data to your /api/generate_docs endpoint (which your app.py is running).

Waits for the JSON response from the backend.

Displays the documentation (or an error message) in the results <div>.

Save the file and exit the text editor.

This is the final file you need to create. After this step, your application is complete and ready to be tested.

